-- _all.sql.recipe
-- A combined _all.sql would be ~778 MB — well over Supabase SQL editor's
-- effective paste limit. Don't try to paste it.
--
-- If you still want one concatenated file for archive/record-keeping, run
-- one of these after `node _extract.mjs all`:
--
-- PowerShell:
--   Get-Content tb_history-part-*.sql, tb_history_key-part-*.sql, tb_web_hs-part-*.sql |
--     Set-Content _all.sql -Encoding utf8
--
-- bash:
--   cat tb_history-part-*.sql tb_history_key-part-*.sql tb_web_hs-part-*.sql > _all.sql
--
-- The concatenation preserves the BEGIN/COMMIT boundaries of each chunk, so
-- running it via psql works:
--   psql "<conn>" -f _all.sql
--
-- The shipping path however remains: paste each chunk into the Supabase SQL
-- editor in the order documented in README.md §4 — that's the lowest-risk
-- load, since one failed chunk doesn't block the others.
